This paper focuses on the development of methods for training robots with physical bodies, specifically in the context of table tennis. This involves incorporating learning into a hierarchical control framework, using both model-free and model-based strategies. The paper also discusses the use of human demonstrations and self-play to train the robot. Given these topics, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY), which are relevant sub-categories.
